abstract: Letter sent to lawmakers from I Charles McCullough III, inspector general for nation's intelligence agencies, says officials perusing emails on former Sec of State Hillary Rodham Clinton's private computer server found information they deem higher level of classification than 'top secret.'
lead_paragraph: An inspector general’s letter says that some of the information in her emails has been determined to have a designation usually given to information about “special access programs.”

headline.main: Hillary Clinton Email Said to Include Material Exceeding ‘Top Secret’
headline.print_headline: Clinton Email Said to Include Material Exceeding ‘Top Secret’
